Notwithstanding the provisions of section three, the Minister, if he is satisfied that it is in the public interest so to do, may—
(a) by statutory instrument suspend the registration of new building societies either indefinitely or for the period stated in the statutory instrument and during the time that such statutory instrument is in force the Registrar shall not register any new society;
