(1) Subject to the provisions of subsection (8), the Governor of the Bank of Zambia shall by statutory instrument direct, from time to time, the minimum amount of liquid funds to be maintained by building societies and every building society shall be bound by such direction, which shall be expressed in terms of a percentage of the total amount of a society's assets reduced by any amount by which the total book value of the society's investments exceeds their total market value.
